<P>
Photo, Bryan Majors sifts the rubble of rental house that he shared with his 
wife and parents south of Elizabeth Lake. Among the personal belongings Velma 
Majors found as she scoured the ashes were porcelain figurines handmade by her 
mother. DAVID BOHRER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
