<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONGRESSMAN BEILENSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Our experience with Rep. Tony Beilenson (D-Los Angeles) has been the exact 
opposite of the impression created by your article ("Beilenson: An Appetite for 
the Big Issues," Part I, June 12). 
</P>
<P>
Tony Beilenson is indeed an intelligent, thoughtful legislator. This explains 
why he has won some tough assignments in Congress as a chair of the House 
Intelligence Committee, a member of the House Budget Committee, and a leader in 
efforts to reform the budgetary process. At the same time, he has shown a deep 
and abiding interest in the issues affecting the Los Angeles lesbian and gay 
community which is a sizeable part of his constituency, and our major concern. 
</P>
<P>
Tony has taken time to focus on many of the legislative issues affecting 
federal AIDS policies, and he has been totally responsive to our community in 
working to make funding and treatments available. He also has a 100% voting 
record on issues related to ending discrimination based upon sexual 
orientation. 
</P>
<P>
Tony has been a truly responsive, concerned and committed congressional 
representative. He has always made himself available to meet with our 
organization to discuss issues before Congress. 
</P>
<P>
Rep. Beilenson is cherished because he places principle before politics. 
</P>
<P>
BEVAN DUFTY 
</P>
<P>
Co-Chair 
</P>
<P>
JACKIE GELFAND 
</P>
<P>
Co-Chair 
</P>
