<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGOURA SPRINTER PLANS TO ATTEND UCLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Ingalls of Agoura High, third-place finisher in the 400 in the state track 
and field championships at Cerritos College earlier this month, has made an 
oral commitment to attend UCLA in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
Ingalls chose UCLA over Cal State Northridge and UC Riverside. The Bruins will 
provide him with a partial athletic scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
"You can't beat the school," Ingalls said. "UCLA has just always been one of my 
dream schools. I couldn't believe it when they started talking to me." 
</P>
<P>
Having run 11.2 seconds in the 100, 22.56 in the 200 and 49.61 in the 400 as a 
junior, Ingalls improved tremendously this year, clocking 10.9 in the 100, 
22.19 in the 200 and 47.89 in the 400, the event in which he won the Southern 
Section 1-A Division title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
