<HEADLINE>
<P>
REBEL CATHOLIC FRATERNITY GETS 8 NEW PRIESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ECONE, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rebel Archbishop Marcel Lefebvre attended the ordinations of eight new 
traditionalist priestsThursday, one year after he was excommunicated from the 
Roman Catholic Church. 
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was conducted by Bernard Tissier de Mallerais, one of the four new 
bishops Lefebvre consecrated in 1988 in defiance of papal orders, creating what 
the Vatican said was a historic split in the church. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinations raised to 222 the number of traditionalist priests in 
Lefebvre's St. Pius X Fraternity, according to Bishop Franz Schmidberger, the 
German cleric who succeeded the archbishop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
