<P>
Egghead Discount Software: The Issaquah, Wash., computer software retail chain 
said it lost $12.1 million during fiscal 1989, contrasted with a profit of $4.6 
million the previous year. However, sales jumped 70% to $342.4 million. The 
company said the principal factors behind the losses were fourth-quarter 
writedowns totaling $11.8 million, a change in an accounting method that 
increased expenses by $4.5 million and additional reserves for future 
writedowns of $4.1 million. 
