144 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florence Griffith Joyner, who caused a sensation with her fashion creations in 
track and field, will design new uniforms for the Indiana Pacers. 
</P>
<P>
Flo-Jo dazzled the sporting world with the one-legged body suits and 
brilliantly colored outfits she wore during the U.S. Olympic trials at 
Indianapolis. She set world records in the 100- and 200-meter dashes in 1988 
and won gold medals at Seoul in those events and the 400 relay. 
</P>
<P>
"We made an agreement that what looks good on Florence won't necessarily look 
good on Greg Dreiling and LaSalle Thompson," said Donnie Walsh, the Pacer's 
president at a press conference in Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Griffith Joyner said she already has come up with about 13 designs for Walsh to 
review. The new uniforms will not be used until the 1990-91 season, after the 
league has had a chance to display them in its merchandise catalogues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
