One-Year T-Bill Rates Plunge: The Treasury sold $9.0 billion of the 52-week 
T-bills at an average discount rate of 7.58%, down from 8.18% at the last 
comparable auction on June 1. The rates were the lowest since Oct. 20, 1988, 
when the one-year bills sold for 7.57%. The new discount rate understates the 
actual return to investors -- 8.16% with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,233.60. 
