<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lower sewer rates: The Irvine Ranch Water District has adopted a 1989-90 budget 
that includes a reduction in sewer rates and no change in water rates, district 
officials announced this week. The sewer service charge for a residential 
customer, now $8.95 a month, will be reduced to $8.35, effective Saturday. The 
decrease is due to lower operating costs and greater revenue, water district 
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
