<LENGTH>
<P>
111 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Community Psychiatric Centers, Laguna Hills, reported that earnings increased 
19% in the second quarter ended May 31, to $23.5 million from $19.7 million for 
the comparable quarter last year. Revenue in the quarter rose 21% to $112.9 
million from $93.1 million. For the first half, earnings totaled $44 million, 
20% higher than the $36.6 million posted for the first six months a year ago. 
Revenue increased 23% to $215.4 million from $174.7 million. Community 
Psychiatric owns and operates a chain of psychiatric hospitals. It also 
provides alcoholic treatment services, operates a chain of kidney dialysis 
centers and owns a home health care services business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
