<P>
ZSA ZSA CHARGED WITH BATTERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zsa Zsa Gabor was charged today with three misdemeanors, including battery for 
allegedly slapping a motorcycle officer who stopped her Rolls Royce on La 
Cienega Boulevard June 14 for having expired license tags. 
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian-born actress was scheduled to be arraigned July 12 on one count 
each of battery on a police officer, disobeying a police officer and having an 
expired driver's license. 
</P>
<P>
Gabor was also charged with two infractions: having an open container of 
alcohol in a vehicle and having an expired vehicle registration. If convicted 
of the battery charge, the actress could be sentenced to a year in county jail 
and fined $2,000. The other misdemeanor charges carry maximum six-month jail 
terms and $1,000 fines. 
</P>
<P>
The infractions are punishable by $100 fines. 
</P>
