<P>
SERWANO BEATS TIGER TO KEEP TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN JOSE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arthur Serwano of Richmond retained his U.S. Boxing Assn. junior-middlewight 
title and remained undefeated by scoring a unanimous decision Thursday night 
over Young Dick Tiger of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Serwano, a native of Uganda, made his record 16-0-1 while Tiger, a nephew of 
the late world champion Dick Tiger, now is 26-8. The bout was held before 879 
fans at the San Jose Civic Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, USBA featherweight champ Lupe Gutierrez of San Jose knocked out Tony 
DeLaRosa of Mexico in the third round of a scheduled 10-round fight. Gutierrez 
is 21-2 with 16 KOs while his opponent dropped to 15-6. 
